    "7353": "Partial CUI Files (Auto Load)",
    "7354": "Customization Files",
    "7355": "Working Support File Search Path",
    "7360": "Specify the folders in which %.*s should look for text fonts, customization files, plug-ins, drawings to insert, linetypes, and hatch patterns that are not in the current folder.",
    "7361": "Specify the folders in which %.*s looks for device drivers for the pointing device, printers, and plotters.",
    "7362": "Specify the folders in which %.*s searches for xrefs. The current project is stored in the drawing using the PROJECTNAME system variable.",
    "7363": "Specify where %.*s looks for help and configuration files, as well as the default internet location.",
    "7364": "Specify the Main customization file location.",
    "7365": "Specify the path and file name of the %.*s help file.",
    "7366": "Contains the drive and path for automatic save files.",
    "7367": "Contains the drive and path for color book files",
    "7368": "Specifies the path for the log file that is created if you select Maintain a Log File on the Open and Save tab.",
    "7369": "Specify the Internet location to be used by the Connect to %s command. This value is stored in the registry. You can also use the INETLOCATION system variable.",
    "7370": "The path and file name for the current device driver configuration file.  This value is read-only and may only be changed using the /c command line switch.",
    "7371": "The network server defined to issue a license from the Autodesk Network License Manager.  This value is read-only and should only be changed by your System Administrator.",
    "7372": "Specify the files that %.*s is to use for creating, checking, and displaying text objects.",
    "7373": "Specify the application file name used to edit MTEXT objects. To use %.*s's internal text editor, specify Internal. This value is stored in the registry. You can also use the MTEXTED system variable.",
    "7374": "Sets the current spelling dictionary. This value is stored in the registry. You can also use the DCTMAIN system variable.",
    "7375": "Specify the path and file name of the custom spelling dictionary. This value is stored in the registry. You can also use the DCTCUST system variable.",
    "7376": "Specify the alternate font to use when a font cannot be located and is not identified in the font-mapping file. This value is stored in the registry. You can also use the FONTALT system variable.",
    "7377": "Specify the font-mapping file used when a font specified by a drawing cannot be located. This value is stored in the registry. You can also use the FONTMAP system variable.",
    "7378": "Specify the files that %.*s uses while printing drawings.",
    "7379": "Specify a default name for plot files when using legacy plotting scripts. Set to \".\" to use the current drawing name.",
    "7380": "Specify the file name of the application that %.*s invokes on completion of a print to file. The application usually spools the print file to a printer. Leave blank when no application is to be used.",
    "7381": "Specify the prolog section to read from the %.*s.psf file when using the PSOUT command. This value is stored in the registry. You can also use the PSPROLOG system variable.",
    "7382": "Specify the path for print spool files.",
    "7383": "Specifies drawing template folder and default template file for new drawings.",
    "7384": "Specify the path to locate template drawing files used by the Start Up wizard and New dialog.",
    "7385": "Specify the drawing template file used by the QNEW command.",
    "7387": "Specify the path for temporary external reference files. If blank, the Temporary Drawing File Location is used. This value is stored in the registry. You can also use the XLOADPATH system variable.",
    "7388": "Specify the folders in which %.*s searches for rendering texture maps.",
    "7389": "Specifies the path for database source files. Changes to this setting don't take effect until you quit and restart %.*s.",
    "7390": "Specifies search path settings for printer support files. ",
    "7391": "Specify the path for printer configuration files.",
    "7392": "Specify the path for printer style sheets.",
    "7393": "Specify the path for printer description files.",
    "7394": "Search Path to find ObjectARX Applications which own custom objects detected during drawing file read.",
    "7395": "Specify the locations to locate tool palette definitions.",
    "7396": "Specifies the path where files are placed when dragging and dropping i-drop content off the web.  When not specified, assumes the location of the current drawing.",
